# Nebula Notes - Cursor Rules

## Project Context

This is a HackTX 2025 hackathon project - a cosmic journaling app that transforms emotions into nebula visualizations using Cloudflare Workers AI.

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 15 + React 19
- Cloudflare Workers + Pages
- Workers AI (Llama 3.1, DistilBERT)
- D1 Database (SQLite)
- KV (Key-Value Store)
- TailwindCSS 4 + Framer Motion

## Coding Standards

- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Prefer functional components with hooks
- Use async/await for API calls
- Add loading states for all async operations
- Include error handling with try/catch
- Use Framer Motion for animations
- Follow cosmic theme (purples, blues, space vibes)

## File Organization

- API routes in `src/app/api/`
- Pages in `src/app/[page]/`
- Reusable components in `src/components/`
- Global styles in `src/app/globals.css`

## Cloudflare Bindings

- `env.AI` - Workers AI
- `env.DB` - D1 Database
- `env.JOURNAL_KV` - KV Namespace

